<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-06-05T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-06-05T05:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">875.00/134: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-05T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 5,
                                        1924—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 5—8:15
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>105. Albanian revolution seems to be succeeding. Details as far as known
                            here are fully covered in Associated Press reports. Copy to European
                            Information Center.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>